    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      36.57,
      560.31,
      487.34
    ],
    "text": "Common tactics used by criminals include: \u2022 Approaching individuals in a friendly manner in public places or on public transport \u2022 Gaining trust by pretending to be acquaintances or well-wishers \u2022 Offering sweets, food, or beverages laced with intoxicating substances \u2022 Using harmful agents such as chemical sprays or chili powder to incapacitate victims To avoid becoming a victim, please follow these safety guidelines: \u2022 Exercise caution when accepting transport from strangers, whether on roads or in public areas \u2022 Never consume food or drinks offered by unknown individuals under any circumstances \u2022 Avoid unnecessary interactions or close associations with unfamiliar persons or groups \u2022 Remain vigilant and safeguard your money, jewelry, and other valuables \u2022 Immediately report any suspicious individuals, vehicles, or activities by contacting 119, 118, or the nearest police officer or station The Sri Lanka Police emphasizes the importance of acting responsibly and staying informed about these guidelines. Public awareness and cooperation are essential in preventing such crimes. The public is kindly requested to share this message widely to help protect friends, family, and the wider community from potential danger. Police Media Division",
